oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Fun - Tammy Wynette performance - 1971-01-13
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance of Fun, written by Carmol Taylor and Tammy Wynette, produced by Billy Sherrill, recorded on January 13, 1971 at Columbia Recording Studio in Nashville, TN, released by Epic on February 8, 1971, and performed by Tammy Wynette (vocal), Jerry Kennedy (guitar), Ray Edenton (guitar), Chip Young (guitar), Pete Drake (steel), Roy Husky Junior (bass), Buddy Harman (drums), and Hargus "Pig" Robbins (piano).
